---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import BgGrid from "@/components/assets/BgGrid.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="border-b border-white/20 divide-y divide-white/20">
    <div class="px-8 py-6 relative">
      <BgGrid />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-black text-white uppercase">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mt-2">Last updated: March 28, 2026</p>
    </div>
    <div class="px-8 py-12 max-w-3xl space-y-10 text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">1. Overview</h2>
        <p>RabbitHole ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information in connection with your use of the RabbitHole browser extension ("the Extension"). Because RabbitHole operates entirely on your device, we do not collect, transmit, or store your personal data on any external server.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">2. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>RabbitHole does not collect, transmit, or have access to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li>The content of the articles, papers, or webpages you read</li>
          <li>Any text you highlight or interact with through the Extension</li>
          <li>Your browsing history</li>
          <li>Personal identifiers such as your name, email address, or IP address</li>
          <li>Any data generated by the Extension's AI features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">All processing occurs locally on your device and never leaves it.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">3. Local Storage</h2>
        <p>The Extension may store preferences and settings locally on your device using your browser's built-in storage APIs. This data never leaves your device and is only accessible by you. You can clear this data at any time through your browser's extension settings.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>RabbitHole does not integrate with or send data to any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services. The Extension does not contain any third-party tracking code.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">The Extension is distributed through the Chrome Web Store. Your use of the Chrome Web Store is subject to Google's own Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">5. Payments</h2>
        <p>Purchases of RabbitHole are processed through the Chrome Web Store payment system, managed by Google. We do not collect, process, or store any payment information directly. Please refer to Google's Privacy Policy for information on how payment data is handled.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>RabbitHole is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any information from children. If you believe a child has provided personal information through our services, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically. Continued use of the Extension after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black uppercase text-lg mb-3">8. Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out to us through the Chrome Web Store listing page.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
